Delicious, and quick and easy to make= Winner! It is important to use only 10oz of challah (or egg) bread and not more else the pudding wont be gooey enough. i used a pound of challah, which i cut into 1/2" cubes. i didnt bother to measure the number of cups. i kept all other elements of the pudding as per the recipe. while it wasnt as gooey as it should be (because i used a pound of bread), it was still SUPER delicious. i will definitely be making it in the future but with the right proportion of bread, and using a combination of whole milk and whipping cream. the half and half doesn't taste too heavy, but isnt the healthiest ingredient.... especially if you plan to indulge every day! the caramel sauce is a must for the recipe. it rounds out the "pumpkin pie" flavor. what i changed about the sauce: added some sea salt + vanilla extract.

