Rating: 4
Just served this at a thanksgiving pot-luck. "This is really good" from a few people :) I'm not an expert cook, so I'll share what I did. I followed the recipe to a T, except I added twice the pumpkin pie spice and cinnamon as recommended by other reviewers. I found some pre-made challah bread at the store. I ended up using one with raisins and one without. I didn't find a good guide on making the bread cubes, so I took the bread fresh and start cutting it into "cubes" as best I could, crust included. I let the bread sit out for a few hours before I mixed it up. I tried folding the bread cubes in the non-raisin one, but I was worried about the bread not being evenly distributed. So I poured the mix on top of the bread cubes on the second one, and worked the pudding around so it filled in around the edges. I stored it overnight in the fridge covered. Cooked it in the morning. The caramel sauce is a definite must, and made it exactly as said (yummy!). Vanilla Ice Cream goes great with this as well. Ended up cooking for about 1hr-1hr15min, and don't forget to give some time to cool! Awesome recipe!

