Pumpking pie is obsolete! This is the most amazing bread pudding ever and about a million times better than pumpkin pie. I've made it twice and found the key is not to use too much bread so it stays nice and custardy. The unbaked mixture should be really, really wet. Being a caramel purist, I initially disliked the brown sugar faux "caramel" sauce but when I made a real, carmelized sugar carmel sauce I found it didn't compliment the flavors as well so I guess it's back to the recipe as written!

Rating: 3
