I make this dish at least once a month during the winter months. It is absolutely unbelievable, and every person that has tried it asks for the recipe. Here are a few simple keys for making this dish exraordinary instead of just really good. First, use very fresh bread and keep it as light and air filled as possible when cubing it (I often tear it gently with my hands). Second, use real butter and full-fat heavy whipping cream for the caramel sauce. Once you try this, you may never settle for regular bread pudding again.

