This recipe was the absolute hit of my autumnal dinner party. I made a few slight modifications, however. I left out the raisins (my husband hates them!) Also, in lieu of cubed egg bread, I used day old croissants sliced in half (about 6 whole). I placed the bottom halves of the croissants in a 9 x 13 glass pan, then poured in approxiamtely 1/3 of the custard over the slices. I then placed the top halves of the croissants on the bottom halves, and filled in any gaps with pieces of additional croissant. I then poured in the reamining 2/3 of the custard. I let this soak for 15 minutes, and pressed down on the croissants to flatten them slightly and absorb the custard. I baked this per the recipe directions. The result was phenomenal - the buttery layers of the croissants make this a light yet pleasantly rich dessert. I highly recommend serving this with the caramel sauce and fresh whipped cream - it truly was a delectable combination. Try this recipe - you will not be disappointed.

