I thought this was just okay, not great. I cut the brown sugar to 1 c, and it was still too sweet. I didn't find it too heavy (at least, for bread pudding) as some reviewers did--I wonder if that's a consequence of using fresh bread. Although this recipe doesn't mention it, most bread pudding recipes call for slightly stale bread, which is less likely to get waterlogged by the custard. If you only have fresh bread, you can dry it out in a 250 degree oven for 15 minutes or so.

