Rating: 3
Bon Appetit, will you PLEASE give readers nutrition information? This is why: I adjusted this recipe to halve the calories, halve the Weight Watchers points and cut 2/3 total fat. The serving size was still VERY generous (more than a cup + 2 T sauce) and the taste VERY rich. As written -- gag! To adjust, first plan to serve at least 8, not 6. In pudding, substitute whole milk for h&h and use 2/3 cup brown sugar. For sauce, use 1/2 cup brown sugar, 1/4 cup butter and 1/4 cup cream. SKIP the powdered sugar and SKIP the whipped cream. Trust me! BTW -- I also used a molasses brown sugar from Zingerman's, very special, worth keeping on hand.

