Rating: 4
This was absolutely fabulous. I served it at a Halloween gathering last night, and people couldn't stop talking about it. I didn't use the caramel sauce that was suggested, but instead I used a white chocolate whiskey sauce, which was outstanding. (1 12 oz. bag of white chips, half can of condensed milk, 3 T of half-and-half, or to desired consistency, and 2 T of whiskey. I made the sauce up off the top of my head, because I needed to use a bag of white chips that I had opened by accident. It was decadent.) I highly recommend this recipe, especially to pumpkin lovers. It was a wonderful alternative to regular bread pudding, and I will DEFINITELY make it again!

